decks.notes: The focus of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creature plays and disruptive spells, all centered around Cloud, Midgar Mercenary as the commander. The strategy is to establish early board presence with low-cost creatures like Cathar Commando and Elite Spellbinder, while also using cards like Ethersworn Canonist to slow down the opponent's game plan. The deck also includes powerful equipment like Sword of Feast and Famine and Umezawa's Jitte to enhance the effectiveness of its creatures in combat. With cards like Armageddon and Ravages of War, the deck can also disrupt the opponent's mana base and gain a significant advantage. Overall, the key concept is to apply pressure early on, control the board, and finish the game quickly with efficient threats.

The main concept of this deck is to utilize spells with a focus on control and manipulation of the opponent's board state and hand. With Lier, Disciple of the Drowned as the commander, the deck aims to take advantage of his ability to reduce the cost of flashback spells and increase their flexibility. By including a wide range of card draw, counterspells, and ways to manipulate mana, the deck can maintain control of the game while setting up for powerful plays with cards like High Tide and Brain Freeze. With a high concentration of instants and sorceries, the deck is able to consistently disrupt the opponent's plans and maintain its own game plan.

The deck revolves around utilizing Cloud, Midgar Mercenary as the commander to lead an aggressive gameplay style aimed at quickly overwhelming opponents. The deck includes a variety of low-cost creatures and removal spells to control the board and apply pressure to opponents. It also features equipment cards like Sword of Feast and Famine and Umezawa's Jitte to enhance the creatures' abilities and provide additional sources of damage. The inclusion of cards like Mother of Runes and Giver of Runes allows for protection and evasion, ensuring the deck's creatures can stay on the battlefield to maintain pressure. Overall, the deck is focused on building a strong board presence and efficiently closing out games through aggressive tactics.
